<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-261-658  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 261 658.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  March 1990 v7 n3 p43(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Client/server OSes: Advanced Netware by Novell. (one of twopreferred client/server network operating systems in LAN Times'1990 reader survey)</TITLE><AUTHOR>St. Clair, Melanie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The $3,295 Advanced NetWare (now in version 2.15) from Novell Inc(Provo, UT) is one of two preferred client/server networkoperating systems (the other being Novell's NetWare 386) in LANTimes' 1990 reader survey.andP;  Novell targets the software atdepartmental or mid-range company networks.andP;  Advanced NetWare 2.15includes such capabilities as support for Macintosh connectivitythrough the bundled NetWare for Macintosh, system reliabilityfeatures such as Hot Fix for disk media defect detection andcorrection, new security enhancements to prevent unauthorizedaccess to network data, a network resource accounting feature,support of up to 100 users and 1,000 concurrent open files perserver, implementation on a dedicated or nondedicated networkserver, and external software for routing to other networktopologies.andP;  The package is compatible with DOS 2.0 and above,OS/2, Windows/386 and PC-MOS/386.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   Advanced NetWare 2.15 (Network operating system) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Network Operating SystemsSpecificationsSystem DesignEnhancementsReader SurveySoftware Selection.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>